					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252611" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1448999094 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Dec 2015 19:44</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2416031">
									

<p>As far as I know, the F-111B was never produced or deployed. Certainly there were never any USAF squadrons. The Air Force doesn't operate carrier-based aircraft.</p>
<p>ETA:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The F-111B was not ordered into production and the F-111B prototypes were used for testing before being retired.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>So, AFAICT, a combat squadron (especially an Air Force squadron) of a non-production prototype (for the Navy) <em>is</em> basically impossible.</p>

							</div>

								
