														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2416050">
									

<p>The Air Force neither had nor wanted the F-111B; they were more than happy with the F-111 base model, which was never required to be a tactical fighter as well as a bomber. In fact, the strike on Libya in 1986 was carried out by F-111s bolstered by F-16s.</p>
<p>On the other hand, was there a wing of Navy F-4s deployed anywhere near LA in '71, or were they all over near Vietnam at the time? Someone might have ordered the strike with the prototype F-111Bs because that was what they had at the time - or they weren't a failure after all, but were quietly commandeered by the Foundation while the development of F-14s was encouraged in their stead&#8230; ;-)</p>

							</div>

								
					
